Author: pius
Content: In addition to what's been mentioned, you should definitely take a solid Linear Algebra course.  Besides the uses for computer graphics (vector stuff) and artificial intelligence applications (singular value decomposition et al), it is really philosophically useful to internalize the concept of transformations and how many non-obvious applications they have.
